======================================================================
OMEGA_2 CONSTRAINT MATRIX STRUCTURE
======================================================================
Constraint matrix has orthogonal rows (each 2-path in exactly 1 constraint).
This is because each 2-path (a,b,c) has a UNIQUE middle face (a,c).
Therefore:
  dim(Omega_2) = dim(A_2) - #{non-allowed pairs with mediators}
  = C(n,3) + 2*c3 - #{non-allowed pairs with mediators}

